problems or aiding them in learning to handle problems when they
surface. Where appropriate, <ENAMEX TYPE="ORGANIZATION">LSC</ENAMEX> <ENAMEX TYPE="PER_DESC">grantees</ENAMEX> refer low-income <ENAMEX TYPE="PER_DESC">persons</ENAMEX>
to <ENAMEX TYPE="ORG_DESC">organizations</ENAMEX> that can help the <ENAMEX TYPE="ORG_DESC">clients</ENAMEX> with their problems -
either to <ENAMEX TYPE="PER_DESC">alternate sources</ENAMEX> of legal assistance or to other sources
of assistance, such as charitable <ENAMEX TYPE="ORG_DESC">organizations</ENAMEX> and social services
<ENAMEX TYPE="ORG_DESC">agencies</ENAMEX>. Through the provision of legal information, programs also
